The pointer parameter 'daemon' is reassigned by the statement 'daemon = MHD_get_master(daemon);'. This modifies the parameter (the pointer itself), which violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 17.8. Use a local variable (e.g. 'struct MHD_Daemon *master = MHD_get_master(daemon);') instead of modifying the parameter.
</scenario>
